<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/11374271-christine-cody"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1551056818i/11374271._UY100_CR18,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/11374271-christine-cody">Christine Cody</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Not at all. I believe you are confusing the movie &quot;The Manchurian Candidate,&quot; which is a political/spy classic from the 1950s. The movie was remade in<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Not at all. I believe you are confusing the movie "The Manchurian Candidate," which is a political/spy classic from the 1950s. The movie was remade in the 2000s, but skip the remake and watch the original...can't be beat. This Inspector Wexford mystery is another great Ruth Rendell book but not related in any way. Thanks for asking!<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

