        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3087590221" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6074373241211290588">The way this book starts is a bit disconcerting because it seems almost horror-like. The Inspector takes a trip to China and green tea visions ensue. The rest of the book is more traditional British mystery format with a death of someone familiar and many connections to the China trip. Overall, a slight step outside the usual pattern, and I think it works to make this different from the typical murder mystery.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


