    <a title="Pete K" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/85403878-pete-k"><img alt="Pete K" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3841804966?book_show_action=true">Feb 16, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pete K" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pete K" href="/user/show/85403878-pete-k">Pete K</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780099328100" href="/book/show/1541910.The_Speaker_Of_Mandarin">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3841804966" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16708691558679000781">I&apos;ve had this book on my shelf for years in an Inspector Wexford omnibus but for some reason never got round to reading it. However, with the libraries mostly closed in lockdown I&apos;ve been working through reading material in the house and eventually got to this book.<br/><br/>It took me a while to get into it because of the opening section in China which is quite different to the other Wexford novels. There were a lot of characters to remember too and I got a bit muddled as to who was who. Once back in Kin</span>
  <span id="freeText16708691558679000781" style="display:none">I've had this book on my shelf for years in an Inspector Wexford omnibus but for some reason never got round to reading it. However, with the libraries mostly closed in lockdown I've been working through reading material in the house and eventually got to this book.<br /><br />It took me a while to get into it because of the opening section in China which is quite different to the other Wexford novels. There were a lot of characters to remember too and I got a bit muddled as to who was who. Once back in Kingsmarkham though the novel took off and the China section slotted into place with the rest of the story. <br /><br />Overall an enjoyable read so I've given it three stars which in my mind is a good read but nothing outstanding. Nice to be back in the world of Inspector Wexford and it's motivated me to read the other story in the omnibus which I haven't yet read (Put on by cunning). </span>
  <a data-text-id="16708691558679000781" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


