<span id="freeTextContainer12201200040146010113">Chief Inspector Wexford has an unusual opportunity to travel to China. On trains and in hotels he meets members of a tour and shares some of their experiences. When he is home again he has reason to call upon this experience.<br/><br/>An older woman is found on the floor of her home, shot to death. Wexford remembers meeting her in China, and thus calls upon the other members of the tour for answers. As is typical of Rendell, the story has twists and complications. Nobody is going to figure it out. It reve</span>
  <span id="freeText12201200040146010113" style="display:none">Chief Inspector Wexford has an unusual opportunity to travel to China. On trains and in hotels he meets members of a tour and shares some of their experiences. When he is home again he has reason to call upon this experience.<br /><br />An older woman is found on the floor of her home, shot to death. Wexford remembers meeting her in China, and thus calls upon the other members of the tour for answers. As is typical of Rendell, the story has twists and complications. Nobody is going to figure it out. It reveals much about people that is not always obvious.</span>
